n></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/woh1yPA</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DOcelot1]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I Get It</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/gKKqIYv</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6jUcinh.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He's done trying and I get it. Doesn't make it hurt any less or make me feel less rejected.

Made me realize we also have shitty communication skills.

Send pet pics, please.

Just quietly weeping into the void and hoping against hope that he changes his mind.

Most Viral edit: Thanks for all the love, helpful messages and the pets  ❤️

Re edit: I've made a therapist appointment for Monday. Baby steps, right?</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gKKqIYv</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[KPuff]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I'm NOT famous (but I hang with famous people) Part 1</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/YlMn7hi</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Hw3h3y6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Going through pics and I thought I'd share a few of my favourites from the last few years ... 

I was signing comics at Golden Apple in 2023 and the owner asks if I want to meet someone in the back ... SAM JACKSON is picking up comics! 

I ask the owner if I'm allowed to have a picture with him. Sam turns to the owner, and (in the Jules from PULP FICTION voice) says, "Why are you asking THIS motherfucker?! I'M the one you're taking the picture with!"

I was kind of stunned and could barely muster a smile LOL But it was great to chat with a legend. He even asked for a signed copy of ARENA MODE!

Best. Day. Ever.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/saePaF6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Co-created a comic with EVANESCENCE lead singer Amy Lee in 2023, and I met her backstage at her concert in Toronto. AMAZING to meet her and the band, who were so kind and welcoming. 

We signed some copies of the book, and took some photos.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/njwePnH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>If you're into cosplayers you probably know ERICA FETT, who I absolutely LOVE! I try to hang out with her at every con we both attend.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ojjXier.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tehani Farr is an INCREDIBLE artist. She's so talented and beautiful. Love her. If you're into fantasy art, definitely check out her work.

Her HEAVY METAL cover was amazing!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/43n4TPI.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>One of the most legendary comic book creators of all time, Walt Simonson. We've never worked on a project together, but who knows what the future holds?

Fun fact: on his THOR run, he created both Beta Ray Bill AND Frog Thor!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ze9OVnV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And one of the sweetest people I know (and cosplayer for my BARBARELLA comic series) Rachie, aka 'Faces by Rachie'. She's a megastar at comic cons -- I did a signing with her at NYCC and the fans were rabid!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KSwHoUK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Apologies if you hate selfies ... to make up for it, here is a SHELFIE.

Jareth wishes you a wonderful weekend. xox

Love and hugs,
Blake xoxo</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/YlMn7hi</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[BlakeNorthcott]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The GFs of Warhammer 40k by Octosoup</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/RU7G9Zu</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tK50GAA.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0QfygdB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tHRaLSM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dlwKwl6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZW7Pnnx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hSb72d2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eLZAOM6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My favorite group is the Sisters of Battle, easily. I don't play the tabletop game, I am mostly into the stories/lore.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TvJIqo1.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZaYUaY1.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rO9lk8Q.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2Ht82Lk.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fclhrcn.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>My second favorite group, the Kasrkin.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/RU7G9Zu</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[LincLoud]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Made himself at home</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/MmtZCCR</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NnUy98l.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/MmtZCCR</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GullahGullahIslander]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>When Cosplayers catch a snow day</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/U1VFCQg</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JrljETY.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/U1VFCQg</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MayMyEnemiesLiveLong]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Someone appears to have a problem with this wedding</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ondBmCT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lPV0OrQ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ondBmCT</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Togeorevin]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Just listen to the message</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/eUK2HzE</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/CrYDY10.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/eUK2HzE</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[roaduardo]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Views from my office</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/AndopvL</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bgoqXvm.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>First day back aboard the University of Washington's R/V Thomas G Thompson and I was greeted with the best sunset! It's been a while if you've followed my adventures in the past, playing in the galley now as a cook rather than an engineer, and motor boats instead of sail, but still working in research and education! (getting poverty wages on tall ships can only last so long before needing to work on ships that actually pay a livable wage!)</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/saTwORX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sunset appreciation club had a strong showing this last trip! We left Guam with a slew of undergrads to complete their senior thesis research and drove in lots of squiggles and a giant circle around Guam</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ffm1hWY.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We deployed nearly every type of science gear onboard for the wide variety of projects so the students can get data collected and process it for their theses (thesises?)</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KV3dsBo.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Found a baby pepper growing in a pepper!
Being cook for ~60 people onboard has been a new and exciting adventure compared to working in the engine room or on deck, every day is an experiment!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VuJh5E4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sunrises at sea also did not dissapoint!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/X8mKUHt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>As is tradition, decorated a Styrofoam cup to send to the bottom of the ocean!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mu6LI5j.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Had a few squalls and some foggy days woth a constant foghorn going off (while I was trying to sleep...)</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JIRr1Ex.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Celebrated Christmas on the ship, so made a Christmas tree cup!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TOuIprW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Guam is beautiful, too bad I haven't gotten to see much more than our commercial pier berth and our navy pier berths...</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rZWnVIq.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tiny cups went down to 5000m
The tiny cup hierarchy is prominent in the marine science fields, more cups on display is a status symbol of how many research cruises you have done</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LF2daYL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tuggy tug dropping off the pilot to get out of port</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tqTLJiw.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>All my ornaments for the trip!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JEMo6g1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tuggy tug tugging alongside us</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Vl9LgRW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sunset alongside at the navy base today</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hIH6KEH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sunrise at the commercial pier today</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9bVvFek.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Art tax! Picked up carving lino blocks a few weeks ago and working my way through the produce!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/AndopvL</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[readingrabbit]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The cow uprising is nigh... or maybe not. Farmer Brown just found a cool stick.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/lKIqtuL</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/YJw2WDp.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/lKIqtuL</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Othagovna]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Another Dump. Snow Day edition.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/jFJUX6j</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/F6VM4W1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></spa